title: SpaceX launches seventh Transporter rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX launched more than 50 satellites early April 15 on the latest in a series of dedicated Falcon 9 smallsat rideshare missions.

title: FAA issues license for first Starship integrated test flight
summary: The FAA has issued a launch license to SpaceX to the first integrated test flight of the company’s Starship/Super Heavy launch vehicle, scheduled for no earlier than April 17.

title: NASA to Participate in Space Symposium, Discuss Moon to Mars
summary: NASA leadership and other experts will participate in the Space Foundation’s 38th Annual Space Symposium in Colorado Springs, Colorado, and the agency will air two NASA events.

title: SpaceX cleared by FAA to launch first orbital Starship flight
summary: The Federal Aviation Administration issued a Starship launch license to Elon Musk’s SpaceX, a crucial final regulatory step that clears the company to attempt an orbital launch of its towering rocket for the first time.

title: Green light go: SpaceX receives a launch license from the FAA for Starship
summary: "So far they’ve done what they need to do with regard to environmental impact."

title: Orbex CEO resigns
summary: The chief executive of European small launch vehicle developer Orbex stepped down April 14 so that company can go to the “next level” ahead of its first launch.

title: Starship ready for historic maiden flight, gains FAA launch license
summary: With SpaceX confirming Starship is now ready for flight, all eyes were on the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) to issue its launch license. That was finally granted on Friday evening.

title: Aerojet gets $215 million to boost production of solid rocket motors used in weapons for Ukraine
summary: The Defense Department has agreed to provide Aerojet Rocketdyne $215.6 million to expand its rocket propulsion manufacturing faciltiies in order to speed up production of missiles for Ukraine, the Pentagon announced April 14.

title: Ariane 5 launches ESA’s JUICE mission to Jupiter
summary: An Ariane 5 successfully launched a European spacecraft on an eight-year journey to Jupiter April 14 on the penultimate flight of the venerable rocket.

title: New reports explain why security in space is fragile
summary: As more nations seek to explore the vast expanse of space, there is increasing competition and congestion in orbit, according to two new reports released April 14.
